  "why": "The paper's methodology and evaluation are focused on testing individual Sequential Decision-Making (SDM) models in isolation. The proposed fuzzer, CUREFUZZ, is designed to find crash-triggering scenarios for a single target model. The experimental section evaluates the fuzzer's performance on several different SDMs (e.g., in autonomous driving, aviation), but each evaluation is self-contained. The paper does not conduct experiments to check if the fault-inducing inputs discovered for one model can cause failures in other models. Consequently, the paper neither incorporates explicit mechanisms for discovering transferable failures nor demonstrates the transferability of any discovered failures.",
